The African National Congress (ANC) says it has noted the letter written by Secretary General Ace Magashule to the President of the ANC Cyril Ramaphosa. Ace Magashule’s temporary suspension from the ANC: Samkele Maseko:  In a statement issued on Wednesday evening, it said the decisions of the National Executive Committee (NEC) and National Working Committee (NWC) stand. ANC National Spokesperson, Pule Mabe says the NEC will be meeting this weekend and will accordingly respond to the Secretary General. Mabe added: “The ANC has requested that the Secretary General respect the decisions of the NEC and subject himself to the discipline of the organisation.” Magashule’s suspension is a big milestone for the ANC: Snuki Zikalala 